eNCA senior reporter Aviwe Mtila is in Komani and filed this report. Courtesy #DStv403 KOMANI, Eastern Cape - Empty, unusable and in disrepair, that's the Lesseyton sports facility near Koman in the Eastern Cape, which cost a whopping 15-million-rand of taxpayers' money to construct. It's been more than five months since it was unveiled by the Enoch Mgijima Local Municipality. A preliminary report has concluded the procurement process and the awarding of the tender was marred by numerous irregularities. eNCA senior reporter Aviwe Mtila shares more details in the video above.   